# macOS design conventions

Per Apple HIG. Needle targets macOS first — UI should feel native, not web-app.

## Ink hierarchy (4 levels)

Mirror Apple's `labelColor`, `secondaryLabelColor`, `tertiaryLabelColor`, `quaternaryLabelColor`:

| Semantic | Role | Examples |
|----------|------|----------|
| `ink-primary` | Body, headings, primary content | Task title, screen title |
| `ink-secondary` | Supporting content | Subtle labels, event labels |
| `ink-tertiary` | Metadata, captions | Sublabels, dates, hints |
| `ink-quaternary` | Decorative, disabled, placeholders | Empty-state hints, off-state icons |

Never use a lower-tier ink for primary content. Reserve `ink-quaternary` for genuinely decorative use — it intentionally fails text contrast at small sizes.

## Type

- Display / headlines: serif (`Fraunces` via `--serif`). Use for screen titles and prompts only.
- UI: `Geist` via `--sans`. 12–16pt range. Tight tracking (`letter-spacing: -0.005em`).
- Code / keyboard hints: `Geist Mono` via `--mono`.

Apple HIG-style font-feature-settings (`ss01`, `ss02`, `cv11`) are already set globally in `global.css`.

## Spacing and density

- Mac apps run denser than web. Use 4/8/12/16 for most padding. 24/32/40 for screen-edge gutters.
- Row height for task lists: 36–44px (current).
- Touch targets: 32px minimum (mouse), not the 44px mobile minimum.

## Motion

- Durations: 100ms (instant feedback), 150–200ms (state changes), 250–300ms (panel transitions).
- Easing: `cubic-bezier(0.25, 1, 0.5, 1)` (already used for gap-drop animations) for natural deceleration.
- Honor `prefers-reduced-motion`. Skip non-essential animation.

## Window chrome and materials

- Titlebar uses native macOS traffic lights (set via Electron `titleBarStyle: 'hiddenInset'`). Do not draw fake lights in HTML.
- Vibrancy / blur (`backdrop-filter`) is acceptable on titlebar and overlays. Keep `saturate(160%)` and `blur(20px)` as the baseline.
- Avoid drawing colored content under vibrant surfaces — Apple's blend mode shifts colored content unpredictably (per HIG).

## Keyboard

Every primary action needs a keyboard equivalent (⌘N for capture, ⌘, for preferences, etc.). Surface shortcuts visually in UI where they matter (e.g. the `⌘ K` hint in the FAB).
